race.comment: The leading barn has four of the six runners and holds all the aces. BOLDINHO (1) was in a different class last time, sitting just off the speed before letting down impressively for a 2.25L win this trip backed off the map. Won an Open by even further and Todd stays aboard.  Carries plenty of weight again but the hat-trick beckons. FIELD OF FLUTES (2) scored two back then sat on the pace last time 2.25L away in second behind the above. Gives himself every chance and can threaten again. SUNZOU (5) brings back-to-back wins at 70 level. The speedy galloper has been kept on the fresh side and keeps improving. Well-bred and the 4kg weight drop brings him into it. FLYING ANNIE (3) resumes for Clark and goes fresh. Good enough and the betting will be key.
